I want a very simple middleware that simply tells me if the client is logged in or not. Basically "does req.user exist?" But if I use the below code, it prints "not logged in" but does not allow the page to load. What is the solution? I'm combing through the req JSON but it's massive
```function user(req, res, next) {
  req.user ? console.log("logged in") : console.log("Not logged in.");
}```

so to sum up – checking/getting the user out from the req object can take a couple of forms, depending on where/how you put it in :man-shrugging:

```req.isAuthenticated()
// or
req.user 
// or 
req.session.user
// or 
req.session.currentUser
// or 
req.session.passport.user```
where / how you put it in depends on your login/signup implementations.

i.e.
```req.get("/bla", isLoggedOutWithCustomRedirectTo("/abc"), () =&gt; {})

function isLoggedOutWithCustomRedirectTo(path) {
  return // bernds logout middleware replacing the "/" by path. 
} ```

